# MANDATORY: Coworker Delegation Rule for Cursor

## Rule of thumb

Cursor agent = thinking. Coworker = I/O.

## Tools

CLI binary: `~/.local/bin/coworker`. Four subcommands:

- `coworker ask --provider <p> --profile <pr> --paths <f1> <f2> ... --question "<q>"`
- `coworker write --provider <p> --profile <pr> --spec "<what>" --context <ref1> ... --target <out>`
- `coworker stats --since 7d --by profile`
- `coworker rtk {install|enable|disable|status}` (optional plugin ‚Äî see RTK section)

Profiles: `code` (default, generic analysis), `datarim` (Datarim artifacts), `social` (posts), `write` (boilerplate). Cost-sensitive tasks ‚Üí `--provider deepseek` (~14x cheaper output vs Moonshot).

## ALWAYS delegate via coworker ask when ANY trigger fires

- Total lines to read >600 (sum across files, not per file).
- ‚â•3 files for one question.
- Any read from `wiki/_raw_/`.
- Bootstrap reads (tasks.md + backlog.md + CLAUDE.md + PRD + plan) ‚Äî one call, not per-file Read.
- `git diff` / `git log -p` output >~200 lines.

## ALWAYS write through coworker write first, then surgical edit

- First draft of PRD, plan, design docs, task-description.
- Articles in `wiki/`, posts in `Social Media/`, ecosystem-site docs.
- Never accept blindly ‚Äî after `coworker write`, read output and edit judgment-parts only.

## File-type policy (critical ‚Äî common friction point)

By default `coworker ask` accepts ONLY `.md`, `.markdown`, `.txt` files. Passing `.py`/`.ts`/`.js`/`.rs`/`.go`/`.sh`/`.mdc` exits 6 with: 'file X (extension .y) is not in the allowed list'.

For code delegation, explicitly add ONE of:

- `--allow-code` flag, OR
- `COWORKER_ALLOW_CODE=1` environment variable prefix.

Example:

```
coworker ask --allow-code --provider deepseek --profile code --paths src/foo.py src/bar.py --question "..."
```

Do NOT retry after exit 6 ‚Äî use the flag from the first invocation when reading code files. Prefer the explicit `--allow-code` flag (override stays visible in shell history).

## RTK plugin (opt-in, Rust Token Killer)

RTK is an OPTIONAL coworker plugin for extra token savings via local `rtk` rust binary (https://github.com/Arcanada-one/rtk). Default-OFF; explicit opt-in required.

Commands:

- `coworker rtk install` ‚Äî prints OS-specific install instructions (macOS / Linux / Windows)
- `coworker rtk enable` ‚Äî adds idempotent hook to `~/.claude/settings.json` (marker `_managed_by: coworker-rtk`)
- `coworker rtk disable` ‚Äî removes hook, settings.json back to pre-enable state
- `coworker rtk status` ‚Äî shows binary path/version + hook on/off

Enable when bulk reads regularly exceed ~5k tokens (logs, code dumps, long diffs). Skip for short tasks.

## NEVER delegate

- Tasks under ~2000 tokens (overhead exceeds savings).
- Debugging, root-cause analysis, race conditions, safety-critical logic.
- Architectural decisions and trade-offs.
- When exact line numbers are needed for Edit (coworker summaries lose them).
- Reasoning about user intent.

## Failure modes

If provider API key unset / out of balance: scripts fail loudly. Fallback to native Read for that turn only. Switch provider with `--provider <other>`.

